Description:
eBOS Technologies Ltd is an innovative and client-focused Information Technology company headquartered in Nicosia, Cyprus, providing advanced e-business software solutions to enterprise customers on a worldwide basis. We seek to hire an outstanding Senior AI & ML Software Engineer to lead our team of AI/ML experts.

Responsibilities

The Senior AI & ML Software Engineer will lead our team of AI/ML experts and undertake/supervise/coordinate the design, development, testing, validation of AI & ML algorithms and their integration in the company’s Enterprise Resource Planning portfolio of services (WiseBOS Suite), as well as in EU-funded R&D projects in which the company participates. In particular, to:
• Supervise and manage the team of AI/ML experts and closely collaborate with our Software Development team.
• Undertake feasibility studies to integrate AI/ML functionalities into software systems;
• Research novel AI/ML techniques to design and develop tailored AI/ML algorithms;
•... Develop datasets to methodologically test the novel AI/ML algorithms;
• Successfully integrate the new AI/ML algorithms and techniques into software systems;
• Take part in related R&D activities of the company, including training, project meetings, contribution to funded R&D projects, etc., as required.

Qualifications, skills and expertise
• MSc in Computer Science or related area (e.g. Maths, Physics, Electrical/Electronics Engineering);
• Preference will be given to PhD degree candidates in above areas, preferably specialised in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning/Deep Learning/Data mining;
• Strong research skills with prior experience in supervised and unsupervised model building and optimisation;
• Research track record in related areas with preference for industrial and/or Horizon 2020 projects;
• Excellent knowledge of Microsoft SQL Server 2016 and above;
• Excellent communication and team management skills;
• Fluency in verbal and written English language;
• At least 4 years of prior industry experience in AI / ML Development

Benefits
• Very attractive salary, based on qualifications and experience;
• Provident fund and national health insurance scheme;
• Access to proprietary knowledge and tailored training;
• Excellent long-term prospects for career & skills development.

Interested applicants should forward their Curriculum Vitae in confidence to the Human Resources Manager

Email: hrmanager@ebos.com.cy

With over 50 products and 1 billion installs worldwide, AIBY is at the forefront of AI development. Creativity and team spirit are the backbone of our company, and thanks to them, we boast such titles as NatureID, HitMeal, Fonts Art, InPulse, and CountThis. Here, you can do the work you enjoy while helping millions of people.

To further expand our horizons and achieve even bigger results in a number of fields, we’re looking for a Machine Learning Engineer to join our team.

What tasks need to be performed:
• The optimization of deep neural networks for fast inference (distillation, quantization, research into new architectures, etc.).
• Training and fine-tuning of multi-modal diffusion models using custom datasets.
• The deployment of generative models using various inference engines like TensorRT, AITemplates, and CoreML.
• Cooperation with the Engineering Team and the visualization and reporting of the results of your research to the Product Team.

Tech stack:

Inference engines ... deployment:
• TensorRT + NVIDIA Triton Server + FastAPI;
• AITemplates + Lightning (FastAPI) + RabbitMQ;
• CoreML - will be a plus.

ML frameworks:
• PyTorch + JAX;
• HuggingFace: diffusers, transformers, tokenizers;

ML/DL approaches:
• Distillation, quantization;
• Diffusion Models;
• Super Resolution;
• Generative Adversarial Networks (adversarial training, perceptual loss);
• Traditional Computer Vision: object detection, classification, semantic segmentation ( will be a plus).

You are a good fit for this role if you:
• Have at least 5 years of experience with Python and 3 years of experience with Pytorch ;
• Demonstrate on-hands experience with the development process in DL and ML (Docker, git, TensorBoard, DVC, Weights & Biases);
• Have experience with a similar stack;
• Prove English proficiency of at least B1

Will be a plus:
• Public activity on Kaggle, GitHub, Leetcode or Social media.
• Software development background.
• At least B1 level of Belarussian/Ukrainian/Russian

